title: Orion spacecraft splashes down in Pacific, completing first Artemis mission
description: The Orion spacecraft, which had no astronauts on board, splashed down in the Pacific Ocean at 12:40 p.m. Eastern off the Baja Peninsula of Mexico under a trio of billowing parachutes.

title: Live updates: NASA’s Artemis I Orion spacecraft returns to Earth
description: The flight has gone exceedingly well, raising hopes for Artemis II, the first flight with crew.
